.TH "SUPPRESSEDERROR" "3JS" "July 29, 2025" "JavaScript" "JavaScript Reference Manual"
.SH NAME
SuppressedError \- SuppressedError
.SH SYNOPSIS
The \f[B]\f[CB]SuppressedError\f[B]\f[R] object represents an error
generated while handing another error.
It is generated during resource disposal using \f[CR]using\f[R] or
\f[CR]await using\f[R].
.PP
Compared to \f[CR]AggregateError\f[R], \f[CR]SuppressedError\f[R] is
used to represent a single error that is suppressed by another error,
while \f[CR]AggregateError\f[R] represents a list of unrelated errors.
It is possible, though, for a \f[CR]SuppressedError\f[R] to contain a
chain of suppressed errors
(\f[CR]e.suppressed.suppressed.suppressed...\f[R]).
It is also semantically different from \f[CR]cause\f[R] because the
error is not \f[I]caused\f[R] by another error, but \f[I]happens
when\f[R] handling another error.
.PP
\f[CR]SuppressedError\f[R] is a subclass of \f[CR]Error\f[R].
.SH CONSTRUCTOR
.TP
\f[B]SuppressedError()\f[R]
Creates a new \f[CR]SuppressedError\f[R] object.
.SH INSTANCE PROPERTIES
\f[I]Also inherits instance properties from its parent
\f[CI]Error\f[I]\f[R].
.PP
These properties are defined on \f[CR]SuppressedError.prototype\f[R] and
shared by all \f[CR]SuppressedError\f[R] instances.
.TP
\f[B]SuppressedError.prototype.constructor\f[R]
The constructor function that created the instance object.
For \f[CR]SuppressedError\f[R] instances, the initial value is the
\f[CR]SuppressedError\f[R] constructor.
.TP
\f[B]SuppressedError.prototype.name\f[R]
Represents the name for the type of error.
For \f[CR]SuppressedError.prototype.name\f[R], the initial value is
\f[CR]\(dqSuppressedError\(dq\f[R].
.RS
.PP
\f[B]Note:\f[R] \f[CR]SuppressedError\f[R] never has the
\f[CR]cause\f[R] property, because the semantics of \f[CR]cause\f[R]
overlaps with \f[CR]suppressed\f[R].
.RE
.PP
These properties are own properties of each \f[CR]SuppressedError\f[R]
instance.
.TP
\f[B]error\f[R]
A reference to the error that results in the suppression.
.TP
\f[B]suppressed\f[R]
A reference to the error that is suppressed by \f[CR]error\f[R].
.SH INSTANCE METHODS
\f[I]Inherits instance methods from its parent \f[CI]Error\f[I]\f[R].
.SH EXAMPLES
.SS Catching an SuppressedError
A \f[CR]SuppressedError\f[R] is thrown when an error occurs during
resource disposal.
Throwing an error causes scope cleanup, and each disposer during the
cleanup can throw its own error.
All these errors are collected into a chain of
\f[CR]SuppressedError\f[R] instances, with the original error as the
\f[CR]suppressed\f[R] property and the new error thrown by the next
disposer as the \f[CR]error\f[R] property.
.IP
.EX
\f[B]try\f[R] {
  using resource1 = {
    [Symbol.dispose]() {
      \f[B]throw\f[R] \f[B]new\f[R] Error(\(dqError while disposing resource1\(dq);
    },
  };
  using resource2 = {
    [Symbol.dispose]() {
      \f[B]throw\f[R] \f[B]new\f[R] Error(\(dqError while disposing resource2\(dq);
    },
  };
  \f[B]throw\f[R] \f[B]new\f[R] Error(\(dqOriginal error\(dq);
} \f[B]catch\f[R] (e) {
  console.log(e \f[B]instanceof\f[R] SuppressedError); \f[I]// true\f[R]
  console.log(e.message); \f[I]// \(dqAn error was suppressed during disposal\(dq\f[R]
  console.log(e.name); \f[I]// \(dqSuppressedError\(dq\f[R]
  console.log(e.error); \f[I]// Error: Error while disposing resource1\f[R]
  console.log(e.suppressed); \f[I]// SuppressedError: An error was suppressed during disposal\f[R]
  console.log(e.suppressed.error); \f[I]// Error: Error while disposing resource2\f[R]
  console.log(e.suppressed.suppressed); \f[I]// Error: Original error\f[R]
}
.EE
.PP
The chain looks like this:
.IP
.EX
       SuppressedError \-\-suppressed\-\-> SuppressedError \-\-suppressed\-\-> Original error
              |                               |
            error                           error
              v                               v
Error while disposing resource1   Error while disposing resource2
    (Disposal happens later)        (Disposal happens earlier)
.EE
.SS Creating an SuppressedError
.IP
.EX
\f[B]try\f[R] {
  \f[B]throw\f[R] \f[B]new\f[R] SuppressedError(
    \f[B]new\f[R] Error(\(dqNew error\(dq),
    \f[B]new\f[R] Error(\(dqOriginal error\(dq),
    \(dqHello\(dq,
  );
} \f[B]catch\f[R] (e) {
  console.log(e \f[B]instanceof\f[R] SuppressedError); \f[I]// true\f[R]
  console.log(e.message); \f[I]// \(dqHello\(dq\f[R]
  console.log(e.name); \f[I]// \(dqSuppressedError\(dq\f[R]
  console.log(e.error); \f[I]// Error: \(dqNew error\(dq\f[R]
  console.log(e.suppressed); \f[I]// Error: \(dqOriginal error\(dq\f[R]
}
.EE
